Two viewers per team each see one of two near-identical scenes laid out on a {{ grid_size }}x{{ grid_size }} grid, where every object is a shape/color/size bundle at a (column, row) cell. The two scenes differ in a small number of planted ways — an attribute changed, an object moved, an object added, or an object removed — and neither viewer can see the other's scene or the list of differences. Over {{ round_count }} rounds they must talk on a shared link channel to discover every difference and submit the list.{% if two_teams %} Two teams compete on the identical scene pair each round: a team must find every difference with no incorrect guesses to be eligible, and among eligible teams the one that exchanged the fewest characters on the link channel wins — so correctness gates the round and compression decides it.{% else %} A team must find every difference with no incorrect guesses; the total characters exchanged on the link channel is the score to minimize.{% endif %}
